%% Helix Thready — Expand/Contract zero-downtime migration flow via migration.Runner
sequenceDiagram
  participant Dev as Author (workable item ATM-NNN)
  participant Run as migration.Runner
  participant DB as PostgreSQL
  participant App as Running services (N-1 & N)
  Note over Dev,App: EXPAND phase (backward-compatible)
  Dev->>Run: Apply([0002_expand]) — add nullable col / new table / new index CONCURRENTLY
  Run->>DB: BEGIN#59; Up SQL#59; INSERT schema_migrations#59; COMMIT
  Note right of DB: CONCURRENTLY steps run OUTSIDE the tx wrapper (see OPEN-DB-03)
  App->>DB: N-1 keeps working (old columns intact)
  Dev->>App: Deploy N — dual-writes old + new
  Note over Dev,App: MIGRATE phase (backfill)
  Dev->>Run: Apply([0003_backfill]) — batched UPDATE, idempotent
  Note over Dev,App: CONTRACT phase (after N is everywhere)
  Dev->>Run: Apply([0004_contract]) — drop old col / constraint NOT NULL
  Run->>DB: BEGIN#59; Up SQL#59; COMMIT
  Dev-->>Run: on failure -> RollbackWith(version, migs) reverses Down SQL
